## Niche
40g+ job-site-safe no-microwave protein lunches for trades and field workers

## Target Buyer
Trades workers, apprentices, and field workers with moving job sites and no reliable kitchen access, who are tired of sandwiches, bars, and fast food and want a cheap, repeatable lunch system

## Core Pain
No reliable microwave or on-site fridge means lunch defaults to low-protein convenience food, boring sandwiches, or expensive eating out; they want something portable, filling, fast to pack, and safe to carry through a real workday

## Desired Outcome
Pack 40g+ protein lunches in 5–10 minutes that can survive the workday safely, feel like a real meal, and cost less than gas-station or fast-food runs

## Pricing
$9–$19 PDF

## Product Idea
* Product Idea: 40g Job-Site Lunch System
* Core Promise: Hit 40g+ protein at work without reheating, using shelf-stable and cooler-packed lunch combos built for real job sites
* Format: PDF system + combo library + grocery list + safety checklist + 10-minute prep guide + cost tiers

## Content Engine

### Top 3 Hook Angles
* 40g protein lunches for a job site with no microwave
* stop wasting $50–$100 a week on work lunches
* job-site lunch mistakes: boring sandwiches, low protein, unsafe packing

### 2–3 Content Series
* 40g Combo Builds
* Bad Lunch Fixes for Trades Workers
* Shelf-Stable vs Cooler-Packed Work Lunch Systems

### Primary CTA Path
Comment keyword on short-form content → link page → low-ticket PDF with combo sheets, cost math, and safety labels

## Validation Signals
* Why people will buy: Daily recurring pain, clear money-saving angle, immediate practical use, and a sharper solution than generic meal-prep content
* Why the format fits TikTok: Strong visual assembly, exact-number hooks, clear before/after contrast, and highly searchable problem wording
* Why the offer can convert cold traffic: The angle is narrow, useful, and specific — trades buyer + no microwave + 40g protein + cost savings + workday survivability

## Constraints
* Trust barrier: Low-Medium; food-safety and realism matter
* Complexity level: Low for execution, Medium for positioning because the safety nuance must be handled well
* Speed to revenue: Fast to test, Medium to stabilize

## Risk Flags
* Credibility risk: Medium
* Saturation risk: Medium
* Platform risk: Medium
* Demand-risk uncertainty: Moderate
* Biggest Risk: Becoming generic “high-protein meal prep” content with no worksite edge
* Main Uncertainty: Whether buyers respond most to protein target, money savings, or trade-specific relevance as the lead hook

